801
00:55:03,280 --> 00:55:06,160
Let's go over them, one by one.

802
00:55:07,910 --> 00:55:08,830
Number one.

803
00:55:10,450 --> 00:55:13,910
The suspect can't use
a gun because he didn't serve in the army.

804
00:55:15,080 --> 00:55:16,540
How is that an error?

805
00:55:17,250 --> 00:55:19,090
The suspect did not serve--

806
00:55:19,170 --> 00:55:22,130
How can an officer distinguish
whether or not the suspect served

807
00:55:22,300 --> 00:55:25,180
when they met at the scene
for the first time?

808
00:55:26,470 --> 00:55:28,260
Who is able to

809
00:55:29,550 --> 00:55:32,020
tell that in a glance?

810
00:55:32,850 --> 00:55:34,980
If you can, give me proof.

811
00:55:40,020 --> 00:55:43,110
CIVILIAN MEMBER

812
00:55:45,950 --> 00:55:46,860
Number two.

813
00:55:47,450 --> 00:55:48,570
Officer Jang.

814
00:55:49,370 --> 00:55:53,120
You seemed certain that
the suspect was willing to

815
00:55:53,240 --> 00:55:54,080
surrender.

816
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:55,210
At the scene,

817
00:55:55,290 --> 00:55:58,710
