when he said "save me."

818
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:01,380
The evidence was recorded by
Lieutenant Oh's body cam--

819
00:56:01,460 --> 00:56:03,130
He could've just said that.

820
00:56:16,270 --> 00:56:18,060
<i>He could've just said that.</i>

821
00:56:21,310 --> 00:56:24,190
I took a sip of water after I said that.

822
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:26,490
No one can tell that I did.

823
00:56:27,490 --> 00:56:30,070
Just like this situation, the body cam

824
00:56:30,160 --> 00:56:32,330
was facing down on the ground,
so we have no video.

825
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:37,330
The audio from the body cam is not fit
to be admitted as evidence.

826
00:56:39,080 --> 00:56:40,290
Number three.

827
00:56:41,710 --> 00:56:44,840
What you said sounded like Officer Yeom

828
00:56:45,340 --> 00:56:49,010
shouldn't have been afraid,
flustered, or anxious

829
00:56:49,090 --> 00:56:50,470
in that situation.

830
00:56:50,550 --> 00:56:52,180
Of course he shouldn't have.

831
00:56:52,260 --> 00:56:54,430
In any situation, an officer must--

832
00:56:54,510 --> 00:56:56,310
The law on self-defense.

833
00:56:56,560 --> 00:56:58,350
Criminal Code 21-3.

834
00:56:59,060 --> 00:57:01,650
"At night or in other
uncertain circumstances,

835
00:57:02,230 --> 00:57:04,400
when feeling fear, shock, anxiety,

836
00:57:04,570 --> 00:57:06,530
or confusion,

837
00:57:07,190 --> 00:57:08,490
one cannot be punished."

838
00:57:10,700 --> 00:57:12,200
In other words,

839
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:15,660
when an incident happens at night
and under uncertain circumstances,

840
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:18,580
when it's a situation
where one feels threatened enough

841
00:57:18,660 --> 00:57:20,540
to feel fear, shock, or confusion,

842
00:57:20,620 --> 00:57:21,920
in those circumstances,

843
00:57:22,710 --> 00:57:26,420
anything the officer does can be viewed as

844
00:57:26,960 --> 00:57:28,170
